    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>First of all , If you are having <strong>File</strong> object then why you need <strong>FileInputStream</strong> to be passed</p>\n\n<p>Second you cannot pass <strong>FileInputStream</strong> to <strong>XSSFWorkbook</strong>, as the constructor can accept the <strong>File</strong> , <strong>String</strong> , <strong>InputStream</strong> , <strong>OPCPackage</strong> and a blank contructor see <a href=\"https://poi.apache.org/apidocs/org/apache/poi/xssf/usermodel/XSSFWorkbook.html\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">this</a>.</p>\n\n<p>As you have already a file object , so you can try below code:</p>\n\n<pre><code>File file = new File(\"T:\\\\SeleniuminputFiles\\\\input.xlsx\");\nXSSFWorkbook wb = new XSSFWorkbook(file);\n</code></pre>\n"
